Answer1>
GIT- GIT is version control system created by LInus Torvalds in 2005 and maintained by Junio Hamano. Used for collaboration, history of modification of code etc. GIT is a DevOps tool use for management of source code. There are two types of version control System CVCS and DVCS. GIT is DVCS.

Answer2>
 Version control systems are software tools that help software teams manage changes to source code over time.
 
 Answer3>
  GitHub is a code hosting platform for version control and collaboration. Owned by Microsoft.
  
  
